# Accessibility Standards (WCAG 2.2 AA) - Freshworks Apps

Ensure semantic HTML, proper focus management, keyboard navigation, and color contrast checks for Freshworks CRM apps that run in iframes.

**Justification:** Inclusive experiences broaden reach and reduce legal risk for enterprise CRM users.

## Core Practices

### HTML & Semantics
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<button>`, `<input>`, `<label>`, `<table>`, `<nav>`)
- Associate form controls with `<label>` elements using `for` attribute
- Use proper heading hierarchy (`<h1>` through `<h6>`)
- Add descriptive `title` attributes for interactive elements

### Keyboard Navigation & Focus
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Implement visible focus indicators (avoid `outline: none`)
- Maintain logical tab order
- Handle focus management for dynamic content (modals, tabs, tooltips)

### Screen Reader Support
- Use ARIA labels/roles only when semantic HTML isn't sufficient
- Provide descriptive button text (avoid generic "Click here")
- Include `alt` text for images and icons
- Use `aria-live` regions for dynamic status updates

### Color & Contrast
- Maintain 4.5:1 contrast ratio for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- Don't rely solely on color to convey meaning
- Test with color blindness simulators

### Freshworks-Specific Considerations
- Apps run in iframes - ensure proper focus trapping when needed
- Integrate with Freshworks notification system for status messages
- Support keyboard shortcuts that don't conflict with Freshworks UI
- Consider mobile/tablet accessibility within CRM interface

### Testing & CI
```bash
pnpm a11y:check
```

### Common Patterns in This Project

#### Entity Menu Apps (Intake Guard)
- Use `role="tooltip"` for help badges
- Ensure notification messages are accessible
- Make status maps readable by screen readers

#### Dashboard Apps (Agent Dashboard)
- Use proper `<nav>` elements for tab interfaces
- Ensure table headers are properly associated with data cells
- Provide keyboard shortcuts for common actions
- Use `aria-expanded` for collapsible sections

